This paper is primarily focused on image super-resolution, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also introduces new methods for amortised MAP inference using convolutional neural networks, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) is also a key aspect of the paper, which is a popular topic in both machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Lastly, the paper involves experiments with real image data, which could potentially fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
